caption.paragraph:
FIG. 16. — 

Verum hoeki
(Gruvel, 1901)

, syntype (MNHN Ci 386); 
A
, tergum; 
B
, scutum; 
C
, upper-latus. Scale bar: 1 mm.

subSubSection.paragraph:
Capitulum (
Fig. 17A
) elongated, length twice the width, occludent margin nearly straight, carinal margin convex. Plates smooth, without longitudinal ridges and thin growth lines, not covering all capitulum, with wide spaces between plates, covered by thick cuticle.

